This paper deals with the computational complexity of the game Phutball, which involves making strategic moves to win against an opponent. This suggests that it could fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), or computational geometry (cs.CG). However, since the paper specifically discusses the complexity of determining whether a player can win the game, computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are the most likely categories. Data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT) are also relevant due to the strategic nature of the game, while computational geometry (cs.CG) may be less likely but still possible given the spatial aspects of the game board.
